devdoc.details: Features such as workplaces for doctors or pharmacists are for future iterations

params._degree: contains a string with the degree of the doctor
params._license: contains a string with the legal license of the doctor
params._subjectId: is the ethereum address for the doctor (same Id as the subject that holds this doctor's personal details)
params.sender: is the address of the admin that set the Doctor's data

params._subjectId: is the registered address of the doctor removed
params.sender: is the address of the admin that removed the Doctor

params.receiver: address of the Subject that received the Rx minted
params.sender: address of the Doctor that minted the Rx
params.tokenId: Id of the Token (Rx) that has been minted

params._degree: contains a string with the degree of the pharmacist
params._license: contains a string with the legal license of the pharmacist
params._subjectId: is the ethereum address for the pahrmacist (same Id as the subject that holds this pharmacist's personal details)
params.sender: is the address of the admin that set the Pharmacist's data

params._subjectId: is the registered address of the pharmacist removed
params.sender: is the address of the admin that removed the Pharmacist

params._birthDate: is the subjects' date of birth, in seconds, from UNIX Epoch (1970-01-01)
params._homeAddressA: is the subject's legal home address (uses 2 bytes32)
params._homeAddressB: is the subject's legal home address (uses 2 bytes32)
params._nameA: is the subject's full name (uses 2 bytes32)
params._nameB: is the subject's full name (uses 2 bytes32)
params._subjectId: is the registered address of the subject (approved for holding NFT Prescriptions)
params.sender: is the address of the admin that set the Subject's data

params.sender: is the address of the admin that removed the Subject

params.to: Address of the account to grant admin role

burn(uint256).details: Burns `tokenId`. See {ERC721-_burn}. Requirements: - The caller must own `tokenId` or be an approved operator.

constructor.details: Using ERC721 default constructor with "Prescription" and "Rx" as Name and Symbol for the tokensWe set up the contract creator (msg.sender) with the ADMIN_ROLE to manage all the other RolesWe increment the counter in the constructor to start Ids in 1, keeping Id 0 (default for uints      in solidity) to signal that someone doesn't have any NFTs

params._subjectId: the registered address of the doctor to retrieve
the registered address of the pharmacist to retrieve

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

returns._0: a RxData struct containing all the Rx Data

params._subjectId: the registered address of the subject to retrieve

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

params.to: address to check for admin role privilege

returns._0: true if @param to is an admin or false otherwise

mint(address,bytes32[12],bytes32[24]).details: Does NOT store a tokenURI. It stores Prescription data on contract (tokenURI is generated upon request)

params._keys: Text lines with the 'title' of each content of the prescription (max 19 characters each)
params._values: Text lines with the 'content' of the prescription (max 61 characters each)
params.to: The id of the subject (patient) recipient of the prescription
Address of the account to remove admin role

removeDoctor(address).details: Only ADMIN_ROLE users are allowed to remove doctors

params._subjectId: is the registered address of the doctor to remove

removePharmacist(address).details: Only ADMIN_ROLE users are allowed to remove pharmacists

params._subjectId: is the registered address of the pharmacist to remove

removeSubject(address).details: Only ADMIN_ROLE users are allowed to remove subjects

params._subjectId: is the registered address of the subject to remove

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.
